      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Colonial Museum Wellington ¶ May 23d 1881 ¶ Baron Von Mueller ¶  ¶ At different times you have called my attention to certain plants, and I have always regretted my inabillity to give you the informat...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.05.23</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From John Buchanan</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M111, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS found with a specimen at MEL in the Gentianaceae foreign unmounted collection, in folder, '<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Gentiana</seg>, New Guinea and New Zealand'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>MS annotation by M: 'Answ 6/6/81'; letter not found.</p>
               </note>Colonial Museum Wellington</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">May 23d 1881</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>At different times you have called my attention to certain plants, and I have always regretted my inabillity to give you the information wanted, some weeks ago I got an opportunity to visit the Mountainous districts of the south Island — and although I have not got time yet to examine much of my collection I hasten to send what I have determined. The Gentian plant I did not collect myself, but rescued it out of a sackful of living Alpines intended for the Botanic Garden, it is much destroyed, and I can only send you a fragment. I have made a sketch<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Specimen is accompanied by a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>sketch, as shown, 16.7 cm x 22.7 cm, labelled 'Erythraea? nat. size',<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and the following note on a separate slip of paper: 'Erythraea? (Gentianaceae.) Drawing sent, natural size, not in flower. Habitat. Tararua Mountain, Wellington, 6000 feet Alt. Snow gone.'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>81-05-23_image01</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as near as I could guess, it was neither in flower or fruit and very much damaged, the branches are in opposite pairs or decussate and I can do nothing more than place it in Gentianaceae from its general resemblance, it may be the Australian plant Erythraea Australis and it will be of much interest to find it in New Zealand.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Caltha species I send notes with the specimens,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Specimens not identified, notes not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I was late for getting many in flower. I have not seen a specimen with a yellow flower they are all white, becoming dirty buff white when dry.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also J. Buchanan to M, 18 September 1879<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 79-09-18c).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Remains</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours respectfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>John Buchanan<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>John Buchanan (1819-1898).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Caltha</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Erythraea Australis</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Gentianaceae</p>
